 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)  Power outages will take place for one hour every other hour instead of the ongoing two hours every two hours from today. The power and energy ministry made the decision at a meeting headed by prime minister Sheikh Hasina in light of the problems faced by households. Hasina was present at her office at the power and energy ministry which happens to be among her portfolios besides defence and establishment. The meeting also decided that the stores and shopping malls would have to close at 7pm, effective Thursday. Those interested to run their commercial establishments after that time will have to power their showrooms with their own generators at their own costs. Abul Kalam Azad, Hasina's press secretary, told the press about the decisions after the meeting. Azad said the prime minister had told ministry officials to expedite electricity generation in order alleviate the ongoing power crisis in Bangladesh. She also reportedly told the officials to find out how large power projects under process could be implemented and executed faster. Hasina also told the power division officials to conduct a mass awareness campaign across the country stressing on the importance of austerity in these tough time
